import MainSection from "../../../layouts/MainSection.astro";
---
<MainSection title="The Pitch">
    <div class="text-display-xs flex max-w-screen-md flex-col gap-4 xl:max-w-screen-lg">
    <div>
        Usually,{" "}<a href="/#savings-calculator" class="cursor-pointer underline underline-offset-4">the cloud cost reduction</a>{" "}speaks for itself. However, if you are looking for a quick way to explain the many benefits and features of Panfactum, we have found success with the following.
    </div>
        <div>
            <span class="font-bold">Tagline:</span>{" "}<span class="italic">Save over 60% on your AWS costs in 60 days &mdash; Guaranteed.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <span class="font-bold">Summary:</span>
        </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4  italic [&_ul]:flex [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:flex-col [&_ul]:gap-4 [&_ul]:pl-8">
        <p>Panfactum is the open source framework for those who want the best possible system for building, deploying, and maintaining software in Amazon Web Services (AWS).</p>
        <p>Users choose Panfactum because it:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Reduces infrastructure and hosting costs by over 60%
            </li>
            <li>
                Provides a secure, resilient, battle-tested core architecture with dozens of bundled add-ons
            </li>
            <li>
                Improves developer velocity and reduce toil
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>In particular, Panfactum is an integrated set of infrastructure-as-code modules, local tooling, and comprehensive guides. Its unique self-hosted architecture enables organizations of any industry or scale to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Quickly setup and production-harden their Kubernetes deployments in AWS
            </li>
            <li>
                Safely and easily deploy over 100 open-source projects that replace expensive, proprietary managed services
            </li>
            <li>
                Extend the system using familiar tooling and open standards such as OpenTofu/Terraform, Nix, and Kubernetes
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            While the framework is completely free, the engineers also sell support plans for those who want world-class experts to manage their Panfactum infrastructure and contractually guaranteed cloud cost savings.
        </p>
    </div>
    </div>
</MainSection>